<Author>tongi
<Content>Necessary, nice enough We stayed at the Terminus for one night because we were flying out from Frankfurt airport the following day (Is there another reason for a tourist to stay in Frankfurt more than once??), and we wanted to be close to the main railway station.Our room was spacious, standard business hotel-style, with a good firm bed and clean, and large-ish bathroom - for EURO 70. The room faced the street, but was not too noisy. I noticed there were more rooms tacked on behind the main building that looked smaller - so I would recommend asking to see your room before you commit yourself. There are many hotels within a few blocks of the station if you don't like what you see.Both the receptionists we met were friendly and helpful - and check-out was midday, which was great for us as our flight wasn't until late afternoon. There was a decent breakfast, and a free internet terminal for guests.One other point ... We paid EURO 3 at the tourism office at the station to book us a room. By the time we walked to the hotel (only three minutes), the booking form had not arrived so we booked in directly with the receptionist, and the EURO 3 was a waste. 
